author: @khanhngocle186
text:
Knowing EXO so many years ago when they debuted for the first time with MAMA as well as listening to many OSTs sang by EXO members, but that's it, I'm not interested in them too much but I really like Chen's voice. When it comes to the pandemic and I was so bored at home to search find fun stuff to watch on Youtube, I saw some clips from EXO members, They are so fun and cute just like my stan SJ, so I look up more, all info about them. Sehunnie is the person who catches my eyes, and he is my bias in EXO, but Suho's voice just captures my heart. I love all his songs in this alb. It's just so awesome. I really feel healed and touched when listening to his songs, it really makes me think about myself, think about the time I'm going through rn while living abroad. I can't express how much I love his alb and at that time, I even wonder why I just love him when his enlistment day was almost next week. So sad so pity for meee! Idk if I'm right or wrong but I can feel his loneliness expressed in this alb, his stress his burden. But I'm happy because at least he expressed it and a new unique color that only belongs to him! Just hope that he will be back happily after finishing his enlistment. 
Hi Jun Myeon Oppa, maybe you will never see my comment, but I just hope that you would not put too much on your back, take it easy, Oppa (you once shared the first thing you did in the morning after waking up was checking your phone to see if any scandals happened EXO, I mean I felt so sad when I heard that). You are a great leader now so now just put yourself in the first place more, do whatever you want Oppa. I wish you could date someone who can share the burden with you and fill out your empty! Everyone will cheer up for you and for sure, I'll be the first one hehe. Can't wait to see you until next year and more new color from you in the future. Hwaiting, Junmyeon oppa!!!

author: @b1llie
text: the past week has been pretty tough. i've been convincing myself i'm fine tho, and i told everyone i was good. today i burst into tears twice and immediately forced myself to stop. it's almost 6am and i've just been stressing all night, on the verge of a breakdown. i told everyone i'd sleep early for once to once again fail them (my health has been a big issue lately and thats what made me cry today too). even just seeing my youtube recommendations was freaking me out and had me so stressed. i was going through my youtube history to try and find a song to calm myself down, and i saw all the live sessions of suho's self-portrait album. the second i saw this song (my fav) i clicked and ohmygod it feels like someone just took 10kg's worth of burden off my shoulders. just hearing a calming song sang in his angelic voice, with the amazing and talented band performing instantly calmed me down. i'm still scared for the day ahead but this makes me feel better. nothing can ever replace how the exo members make me feel. just hearing Suho immediately makes me think of comfort and feeling safe. god bless these people for making such amazing music that helps so so many people so much. to anyone else who's struggling, this'll eventually pass too. the exo-eri fam have got your back :)

author: @norlinsunga1504
text:
The last time I fell in love with an album was with Ronan Keating's 1st album. 

This is Junmyeon's 1st solo album and trust me, what he envisioned the album to be, is what the album came out to be. He is into the arts and so he wanted his solo act to be one.

Every song, meticulously curated. 
Lyrics, carefully crafted. 
It's a self-love project with unlimited love to give.

Even the MVs, the live sessions are parallel to the story he wants to tell.

#justiceforselfportrait
#suho
